{
  "texts": [
    "Selecting high-efficiency inverters, implementing cooling systems, and efficient component design address heat effects.",
    "Wiring and Conductors experience heat generation due to electrical resistance, with conduction and convection causing energy losses.",
    "Proper sizing, rating of wiring, and efficient component design minimize these losses.",
    "Batteries in off-grid systems generate heat during charge/discharge cycles, with conduction and convection as heat transfer mechanisms.",
    "Issues include reduced efficiency and shortened lifespan, addressed through temperature monitoring and battery cooling systems."
  ]
}